This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of natural language processing (cs.CL) as it deals with morphological tagging, which is a subtask of natural language processing. Additionally, the paper proposes and compares different neural architectures for this task, which falls under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of neural networks also suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to the sub-categories of neural networks (cs.NE) and computer vision (cs.CV), but these are less likely as the focus of the paper is on natural language processing.
